A very interesting starter card, one of the only ones I can think of between downfall and the base game that costs 3. On its own, it effectively deals 20 (26) damage over 2 turns, while giving you 1 turn of affliction to work with (with the weak being more valuable in most cases, since following up on the vulnerable is difficult after spending 3 energy). That is a nice chunk of damage that can really help with the early game, though it is a skill into nob, and the weak will be blocked against sentries (which lowers the damage to just 1 turns worth). At least it's a high damage skill into nob that can help close the fight out, and the weak can be really useful to mitigate rage. It's also great into lagavulin. Fuel the fire, emerald torch, and a potential boss swap into an energy relic can all make following up on YAM! with more doom or attacks possible, which often really lets the card start to become more than the sum of its parts. It can become a very effective part of a doom stacking/affliction engine if you find a few more ways to apply conditions or efficient ways to apply doom.

The big drawback here is the cost. There will be times where playing this will cost you chip damage in the early game, or where you simply can't afford to cast this because you need to block instead. There is a big difference in fights where you draw fuel the fire before this, which lets you cast YAM! more comfortably, allowing you to capitalize on the vulnerable and block if you need to on the same turn. Reserves in general are a really great way to support this card (and all the expensive cards on collector) as well as taking 4th energy relics/boss swapping aggressively. With the last nerf to fuel the fire's upgrade, I tend to upgrade this first, as the +6 is very solid in the early game. Great with pyramid to help cast it when you can afford to as well as stack the doom more effectively. Snecko eye  is ridiculous as well (true for collector as a whole).
